            PV NAMING CONVENTION
            ====================

The convention for PV naming is as follows:

    $(P)$(H)$(F)$(D)

    Where:
        P - Prefix
        H - Hardware, instance number (2 digits)
        F - Functionality, instance number (2 digits)
        D - Datatype,direction, instance number (2 digits)

    Notes:
        1. All instance numbers start with 01.

    Example:
        ebr:ath01:reg01:inpb
        ^   ^     ^     ^
        |   |     |     |
        |   |     |     +--- Type (i.e. input byte)
        |   |     |
        |   |     +-------- Functionality instance 01
        |   |
        |   +------------- Athena hardware instance 01
        |
		+---------------- EPICS brick prefix

$(H) Hardware types, instance number (AA is instance number)
    athAA   - Athena processor
    rmmAA   - Ruby-MM module
    pmmAA   - Pearl module
    gmmAA   - GPIO-MM module
    sadAA   - Smart A/D
    scalAA  - Scaler
    femAA   - Femto amplifier
    pf4AA   - PF4 filter
    sftAA   - Soft
    gdioAA  - Generic Digital IO
    wdioAA  - Weeder DIO
    wtciAA  - Weeder TCI

$(F) Functionality,module instances (BB is instance number):
    anaBB   - Analog IO
    senBB   - Sensor input
    digBB   - Digital IO
    ampBB   - Amplifier
    filBB   - Filter
    seqBB   - Sequencer
    regBB   - Register
    scalBB  - Scaler
    pioBB   - Programmable direction digital IO
    fixBB   - Fixed direction digital IO
    auxBB   - Auxiliary programmable direction digital IO

$(D) Type (record,data,direction), instance number (CC is number)
    aiCC  	- Analog input
    aoCC  	- Analog output
    biCC  	- Binary input
    boCC  	- Binary output
    ctlCC	- Counter control
    ctrCC	- Counter
    muxCC 	- Multiplexier

    inpb    - Input byte (8 bits)
    inpw    - Input word (16 bits)
    inpl    - Input longword (32 bits)
    outb    - Output byte (8 bits)
    outw    - Output word (16 bits)
    outl    - Output longword (32 bits)

    ***     - Datum (i.e. functionality)
